				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can make (or buy) a connector for the expansion port on the front of the Famicom that you can connect two NES controllers to. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXuxNjXNKkw" class="postlink">Here's what mine looks like</a>. That way you don't have to destroy any original parts.<br /><br />Yes, the controllers are compatible, they use the same set of connections for either the Famicom or NES, though obviously the NES second controller can't produce the microphone signal.</div>

